=============Valid Palindrome========================

class Solution {
    public boolean isPalindrome(String s) {
        s=s.toLowerCase().replaceAll("[^a-z0-9]","");
        //[^a-z0-9] reverses all the characters that are not letter or digits
        //StringBuilder--->reverse is a method used to reverse a string
        String rev=new StringBuilder(s).reverse().toString();
        //Checks the String is same or not
        return s.equals(rev);
    }
}
Example 1:

Input: s = "A man, a plan, a canal: Panama"
Output: true
Explanation: "amanaplanacanalpanama" is a palindrome.
